caption:
I recently watched an interview with @joannacoles (previously editor in chief of Cosmo and now chief content officer of Hearst Magazines) and she responded to a question about how to balance work and being a mom. She said that there is no such thing, it's all about prioritizing. Some days you have sick kids and need to make them a priority and some days you have a big project or deadline and that will be a priority, but there is no such thing as balance. Tell me, do you agree with her?

Normally I do abstracts and keep them for myself or paint commissions for client projects. Last week I wanted to do something lighter that could do be done quicker. I had these adorable wooden elephants from @acmoorecrafts in the boys craft bins I knew they would be the perfect project! Each little one came out completely different and I got to play around with different patterns and colors! I wasn‚Äôt sure what to do with all of them afterwards when many of my followers on Instagram stories gave me the idea of Christmas tree ornaments! Now I‚Äôm still in denial that school has started and Fall is quickly approaching, but I guess it‚Äôs never too early to think about Christmas! Can‚Äôt wait to make some more!  #craftymom #diycrafts #getyourpainton #easycraft #diyornaments #showmeyourstyle #hbcolor #hgtvmagazine #apttherapy #whybuywhenyoucandiy #heyhomehey #myboldhues #preppystyle #elephantart #colorplay #colorfulhome #diydecoration #diydesigntherapy

Bio: Interior decorator & blogger at Effortless Style Interiors. Loves color & pattern. Wife and mom to two sweet boys living in the suburbs of NYC.
caption: Faux or real? How do you feel about faux flowers? I think that when it comes to arrangements in a vase you must go real! I treat myself to fresh flowers pretty much every week. It‚Äôs so easy when you find them @traderjoes ! But when it comes to potted plants I think it‚Äôs okay to go faux. Typically potted plants are more expensive and require more TLC. As a busy mom I don‚Äôt have time for all that or the green thumb. Going faux helps give me the look I want without the headaches. One day when I have time to tackle the precious TLC of a plant then I will go real. Until then let‚Äôs go for faux and fabulous!!!

caption:
Istanbul is one of my favourite European cities, if not my favourite. We travelled Europe for 2 months together last year and Istanbul was the last place we visited before going our own ways. We were warned by countless people that it would not be safe as it was only a few weeks after the military coup. There were very few other people travelling Turkey while we visited and definitely not two or three girls travelling alone. Although I do think safety is essential, I'm so glad we ended up going anyway. Turkey has so many breathtaking places to visit and we were lucky enough to see them without the crowds of tourists. The Grand Bazaar was a highlight of Istanbul for me. We walked through the maze of small shops, taking in the overwhelming sites of Turkish rugs, ceramic dishes, brightly colored lanterns, Turkish flags, clothing, and antiques.  Numerous shopkeepers tried to lure us to their shops. ‚ÄúWhere are you from?‚Äù "You droped something" we'd turn around "my heart". We ended up coming away with a little too much Turkish tea but it was such a great experience. .
.
.

caption:
This temple is located high on the mountain Lempuyang.  It‚Äôs easy to see why the mountain is considered one of the most spiritual places in Bali, with its old Hindu temples and the incredible view of mount Agung. .
.
As per usual nothing went according to plan for us. We got up in the dark, hopped on our scooter and followed google maps up a mountain. This was the twistiest, most windy road, filled with potholes and covered with mud. No easy feat for two scooter novices. Eventually google told us we had arrived, buuuut there was definitely no temple to be seen. Instead we were in a 10 hut village where nobody seemed to have ever seen a white person let alone understand us. In the end we had to drive our little scooter back to town and catch a taxi to the temple. But we‚Äôll just have to say this was another adventure to add to our list to laugh about. . .

The detailing is fabulous but the down side for me is that the instructions make you build it as a left hand drive and not right hand drive changing it isn't a problem what so ever and I would have liked to have either seen a set of suicide doors or standard rear doors but other than that brilliant! Easy to build and goes very well with my #wilkoblox red bus . It goes to show that you don't have to purchase expensive leading brand sets when you can get the bus and cab for a total of ¬£6.50

We are at it again! The AAA Ltd have another exciting new Auction just for you, and just in time for the new show season and breeding... Tuesday 17 July! 
AUCTION ITEM: EQUILUME LIGHT MASK

The Equilume Light Mask is an individual headpiece for horses that provides timed, low level blue light to a single eye to effectively deliver all the benefits associated with long summer days. Scientifically validated and veterinary evaluated, mobile blue light therapy affords owners the benefits of ease of management, and horses the freedom of natural behaviour and improved health and well-being.

Generously donated by @equilume 
All proceeds from this Auction go to the AAA Ltd 2019 National Appaloosa Championships

caption: My name is Adine, and my @instagram page is my highlight reel. I‚Äôm dealing with challenges and emotions I‚Äôm not conveying on this platform because it doesn‚Äôt seem appropriate. I assume you are too, so I try to be as kind as possible to everyone that crosses my path. I‚Äôm grateful for every bump in this road we call life because it‚Äôs made me the tough woman I am today...well equipped to deal with anything thrown my way. I‚Äôm thankful for my adorably loving 5 year old, who loves me no matter how messy the house is and forgives me for being a few minutes late picking her up. Today I‚Äôm so grateful for that B reel. caption: To anyone grinding right now, feeling hopeless, ready to give up... I‚Äôm here to tell you do not stop hustling! It just takes one person, one brand or one investor to change your dreams into reality ‚ù§Ô∏è people always say ‚ÄúI‚Äôll come to your business‚Äù but in reality they never do - it‚Äôs about not depending on those kinda people to pay your bills or determine your worth! There are going to be days where you cry yourself to sleep, are dirt poor, wonder if this is the right decision BUT at the end of it - effort will never betray you! Your time is coming üòå over a year ago I was depressed, just fired from @sephoracanada, confused about my career... here I am today halfway to becoming a Skin Specialist, launching my business/adding services & in a much better place mentally ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ SUPPORT SMALL BUSINESSES - SUPPORT MICROINFLUENCERS - SUPPORT LOCAL ARTISTS üó£ #beautywithbodden #motto #realtalk

Name: beautywithbodden
Bio: √∞≈∏‚Äú¬ç Downtown Toronto √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Äû Pro Makeup Artist √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Ä∞ Future Skin Specialist √∞≈∏¬ß‚Äì√∞≈∏¬è¬æ√¢‚Ç¨¬ç√¢‚Ñ¢‚Ç¨√Ø¬∏¬è Skincare & Beauty Blogger √∞≈∏‚Äô≈í Contact/PR: anika.bodden@gmail.com
caption:
I wanted to take a moment to say I‚Äôll be absent from social media for the next few days! 
From the beginning of October I‚Äôve been suffering from suicidal thoughts while also trying to recover from an eating disorder that completely took over my life... people think because you have all this makeup, skincare, etc that you should be happy but for me that is not it... I love what I do but I‚Äôm also conscious that it causes me to feel my worth isn‚Äôt good enough or that brands like @anastasiabeverlyhills or @bhcosmetics or @fentybeauty will never notice me because I don‚Äôt have the look other girls have/the equipment/the cut creases/the followers/the tv show by @kimkardashian/the body of @khloekardashian ... feeling suicidal makes you isolate yourself, i feel constantly like a burden, I feel as if life would be better if I wasn‚Äôt alive.. so while I love the beauty industry and brands suddenly wanting to care for microinfluencers/POC - I also know Instagram can be toxic for my own mental health and that comes first. I hope to anyone else struggling that - some days are better than others, you are not alone, you matter and I truly do understand sometimes why people cannot take it because life gets to be far too much... I love my friends/family who have supported on this journey & today I‚Äôm choosing #recovery ‚ù§Ô∏è #beautywithbodden

caption:
@neutrogena / @neutrogenacanada Hydro Boost Whipped Balm Review ‚Ä¢
Where can you purchase this product?
@shoppersdrugmartofficial / @walmartcanada / @rexalldrugstoreofficial ‚Ä¢
What is the price range? $9.99-$12.99
‚Ä¢
Who is this marketed for? 
Dry to very dry skin OR dehydrated skin (skin lacking water) ‚Ä¢
What is the key ingredient in this line?
Hyaluronic acid (please note this product contains dimethicone and parfum) ‚Ä¢
How does the product feel?
Extremely light weight, it melts into the skin within seconds and keeps my skin hydrated ‚Ä¢
What are my thoughts?
Honestly I want to love this product so much, it is amazing and for an affordable price point it is great... BUT unfortunately it contains parfum which is extremely strong and causes a trigger to my migraines/allergies/asthma. To combat the fragrance I have to wash my hands immediately after use and layer a lotion on top.
‚Ä¢
Would I repurchase? 
Yes but I‚Äôll be looking for the fragrance free version which I‚Äôve been told is available for purchase
‚Ä¢
Would I recommend to a friend?
If someone suffered from extremely dry skin, takes a lot of hot baths/showers, their skin needs more hydration yes BUT if they don‚Äôt like fragrance this isn‚Äôt the product for them
‚Ä¢
What is my overall rating?
2/5.. the parfum really is why I have to rate this product so low.
‚Ä¢
Have you tried this product? Have you tried any other products from the Hydroboost line? #beautywithbodden #neutrogenahydroboost #neutrogena ‚Ä¢

Translation = my house won‚Äôt be clean until August. üòú Good luck to all you moms out there and to all you moms like me who are working from home with kids home for the summer....I see you. Name: ccandmikecreative
Bio: High School Sweet √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Äî√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s makin √∞≈∏¬è¬° Pretty In Tulsa | Lifestyle & Design Blog | Author of Magnetic   (YA fiction) | Follow along with our crazy crew √¢¬¨‚Ä°√Ø¬∏¬è |
caption:
GETTING REAL WITH YOU GUYS: Last week I posted a picture of myself and got some negative feedback. I could have felt inadequate, insecure, questioned myself, or even decided to never post a picture of myself ever again. But you know what? I‚Äôm doing the exact opposite instead. If you would have told me two years ago when I started this account that I would post a picture of myself for 50K or more people to see, I would have told you you were crazy. But you know what is so freeing? Feeling confident in your own skin. I‚Äôm not everyone‚Äôs cup of tea, and that‚Äôs ok. I‚Äôm not a small girl. I‚Äôm 5‚Äô 10‚Äù tall and I‚Äôm a size 12 on a good day. This body has given birth, three times. This body has had the strength to bring a child into this world without so much as a Tylenol. As I raise my children and specifically my daughter, I am constantly speaking into her life, telling her to EMBRACE WHO HER CREATOR CREATED HER TO BE. I constantly tell her not to compare herself to others because ‚Äúcomparison is the thief if joy.‚Äù I constantly tell her that when she compares herself to others and thinks - if only I was skinnier like her, or if only I was shorter like her, or if only I could play sports like her, or if only I had her beautiful hair color - she slaps her Creator in the face. It‚Äôs like saying - God, you didn‚Äôt do a good enough job on me. No, He did a perfect job when He created each and everyone one of us and when you embrace who YOU were created to be instead of constantly comparing, that is where you find confidence, joy and happiness. 
So this is me, practicing what I preach to my daughter. This is me choosing not feel inadequate because of someone unfollowing me. This is me doing what I love to do. So many women  have asked me for swimsuit recommendations and I find a lot of joy out of sharing classy mom-friendly swimsuits with our followers. So that‚Äôs what I‚Äôm doing. I‚Äôm on the blog with all my summer faves and I‚Äôm also right here just reminding you - You don‚Äôt have to be everyone‚Äôs cup of tea and you will only make yourself miserable if you try to be. YOU DO YOU. And remember - you were created perfectly @liketoknow.it  http://liketk.it/2w6gH #liketkit

Name: ccandmikecreative
Bio: High School Sweet √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Äî√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s makin √∞≈∏¬è¬° Pretty In Tulsa | Lifestyle & Design Blog | Author of Magnetic   (YA fiction) | Follow along with our crazy crew √¢¬¨‚Ä°√Ø¬∏¬è |
caption: Truth be told I did NOT want to post this picture. That is, Until my daughter called me out in a BIG WAY. You see, I was feeling great about myself when I put this outfit on and looked in the mirror. I felt trendy and fun if I‚Äôm being honest. I felt so good in fact, in my new high waisted jeans, that I thought I‚Äôd write a blog post for y‚Äôall. So... I went out and had my daughter snap a few pictures for me. After taking a few, I looked in the camera and immediately started criticizing myself - ‚ÄúUgh, you look fat in those jeans. You have gained too much weight. You‚Äôre a size 14. You can‚Äôt pull those jeans off after all. Forget the blog post. No way am I posting those pictures.‚Äù And much to my embarrassment, I even verbalized some of those criticisms aloud for my baby girl to hear (just that I didn‚Äôt want to do the blog post anymore). Then I heard my daughters words like a knife, cutting through my self-hate and inner negativity -‚ÄúMom, you always tell me that God created me In His Image and that we are perfect and beautiful just the way HE created us.  I think you look really pretty.‚Äù WOW. In other words, PRACTICE WHAT YOU PREACH MOM.  So this is me, posting a picture of myself in high waisted jeans. I‚Äôm curvy and have many imperfections and this summer my son told me ‚ÄúMom, the backs of your legs aren‚Äôt smooth anymore.  They have bumps ALL over.‚Äù üòÇüòÇ. And you know what, I‚Äôm embracing all the imperfections and choosing to love myself in spite of them. And I‚Äôm going to remember that I‚Äôve got little eyes and ears listening to every word I say.  You see, I was preaching self- love, acceptance, and telling my daughter - ‚ÄúEmbrace who God created you to be.... But my goodness, I wasn‚Äôt living that out in my own life and I got TOLD. So this is me, practicing what I preach and choosing self-love over self-doubt, criticism, and a negative internal dialogue. Thanks for the words of wisdom little momma. YES, He did create me perfectly, and don‚Äôt forget... He created YOU perfectly too, so don‚Äôt slap your creator in the face. Oh and PS I wrote the blog post after all (üòú link in profile) http://liketk.it/2x7AR #liketkit @liketoknow.it

Bio: High School Sweet √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Äî√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s makin √∞≈∏¬è¬° Pretty In Tulsa | Lifestyle & Design Blog | Author of Magnetic   (YA fiction) | Follow along with our crazy crew √¢¬¨‚Ä°√Ø¬∏¬è |
caption:
Throwing it back to fall 2016 (I had just started this account) with this pic of our fall master bedroom. This was the room that started it all I guess you could say. I remember posting this room and getting a message from @onekingslane asking to feature it then saying they wanted my design tips. I was like üôÖüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüôÖüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüôÖüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è ‚ÄúUm excuse me what? I can‚Äôt give design advice.‚Äù Life is a funny, beautiful journey isn‚Äôt it? With so many unexpected twists and turns along the way. I never would have thought I would be where I am two years later...designing people‚Äôs homes and restaurants and with some major big announcements coming up soon. Sometimes it scares me. Sometimes I feel inadequate. Sometimes I feel like I took the wrong road and I need to check my map and turn around to find a road that feels familiar again. Just keeping it real because y‚Äôall know that‚Äôs what I do.  But today in church I felt prompted to write these words: ‚ÄúGod lead the way, and I‚Äôll follow. Open the doors and I‚Äôll continue to walk through them.‚Äù Sometimes I feel a little lost. Like I‚Äôm not sure where I am or where I am going. But one thing I know without a doubt.... He has opened these doors for me and I‚Äôm going to find the courage to keep walking through them.  Thank you - THANK YOU for being on this journey with me.  You guys mean the world to me. I‚Äôm going to have some big announcements and exciting news coming over the next few weeks and it would mean the world to me if you guys would come along on this journey with me, just like you have these last two years. Y‚ÄôALL DA BEST. No really, you‚Äôre the best.

Bio: High School Sweet √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Äî√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s makin √∞≈∏¬è¬° Pretty In Tulsa | Lifestyle & Design Blog | Author of Magnetic   (YA fiction) | Follow along with our crazy crew √¢¬¨‚Ä°√Ø¬∏¬è |
caption:
Funny story: for 48 hours my Instagram account was screwed up and I couldn‚Äôt post to stories and I was like omg NOOOOOüò≠üò≠. Then I started cracking up at myself because I remembered how ticked off I was when Instagram rolled out stories. I was so dang mad at another change from insta. Now I love them and they are an important part of our business! It just made me think about how resistant we are to change at times. And how much easier life is if we just roll with the punches and have a long term perspective. üíó. I read this quote recently and loved it : ‚ÄúChange is hard at first, messy in the middle, and gorgeous at the end.‚Äù ~Robin Sharma. 
I mean, preach. This perfectly describes the past two years of our life, especially when it comes to CC and Mike, starting and owning a business together, embracing all the changes that have come our way, and learning to run a business together without killing each other (ha! Yep you read that right... did you really think we never fight? I mean we are TOTAL OPPOSITES after all!) .  It‚Äôs been hard, messy in the middle, but you guys....lately it‚Äôs starting to feel gorgeous. It‚Äôs just a reminder to me to ease into change. Sure it‚Äôs ok to struggle and feel afraid and even mourn the loss of what was... but you guys, beautiful things happen when we embrace change in life. 
______________________________
Speaking of change, sharing my favorite fall photo of our Good remodel from last year.  What a change happened in that house! This project still has my favorite before and after a of all time üíó

Bio: High School Sweet √∞≈∏‚Äô‚Äî√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s makin √∞≈∏¬è¬° Pretty In Tulsa | Lifestyle & Design Blog | Author of Magnetic   (YA fiction) | Follow along with our crazy crew √¢¬¨‚Ä°√Ø¬∏¬è |
caption:
‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt be a good mom AND be a successful business woman.‚Äù That‚Äôs what my inner critic says to me these days. Tell me, why is it soooo darn easy to listen to our inner critic and so darn hard to say positive words of affirmation to ourselves? It takes work: hard, painful, intentional  work to silence our inner critics. But I‚Äôm determined to do that work and I‚Äôm hoping you guys will do the work with me! What does your inner critic say to you? What lies does that evil voice try to convince you of? What negative thoughts does it plant in your mind?  For me, my inner critic goes right for the jugular - motherhood. It tells me that I can‚Äôt run a successful business and be a good, loving, and present mother. It tells me I‚Äôm a failure as a mother. But I‚Äôm fighting back. Our preacher @craiggroeschel is doing a sermon series on the power of our minds and thoughts right now and two weeks ago he said this: ‚ÄúThe life you have is a reflection of the thoughts you think. You can‚Äôt have a positive life with a negative mind.‚Äù Can I get an AMEN?! So this is me being vulnerable and telling you what my greatest fear is. This is me telling you that we have a big launch coming in two weeks and I‚Äôm terrified and excited all at the same time. And this is me telling you my inner critic has been working over time, telling me I can‚Äôt pull this off but even more so, that if I do, I will be a failure as a mother.  It‚Äôs hard, but I‚Äôm fighting to silence my inner critic. I‚Äôm trying to replace those negative thoughts with positivity and truth - ‚ÄúNO. I am fearfully and wonderfully made. God made me creative. He has opened these doors that I am walking through. I am a good, loving, mother. I am teaching my children passion and sacrifice and hard work ethic and most of all, to have the courage to pursue their dreams. I CAN be a good mom and be a successful business woman. I can have balance. I CAN.‚Äù You guys, I‚Äôm fighting my inner critic. Won‚Äôt you fight yours too, with me? üì∑: @brasspennyphotography __________________________________

caption:
FUN FACT: We designed our entire house around our rectangular pool.  It was literally the first thing I told our architect- that I wanted a rectangle pool right smack dab in the middle with the house stretching around it.  It was not easy to get it on our city lot the way we wanted and we actually had to wait 6 months longer for the architect to redraw the plans (by hand) because his first draft didn‚Äôt allow for the rectangular pool. I‚Äôm an extremely impatient person by nature and almost talked myself out of my original vision (the rectangular pool) so that we could just move in more quickly.  But deep down, I knew I would have always regretted it.  So... wait we did and as you can see, we made the pool I originally envisioned work, finally.  Unfortunately we had to give on some garage space which Mike Miller isn‚Äôt thrilled about but I say the pool is soooo worth it don‚Äôt you?! üòúüòâüíóüí¶üèñ

caption:
This post has been a long time coming. Many of you asked me about my CoolSculpting experience. Here I am sharing my personal story ‚ù§Ô∏è Honestly, I have always gotten into a great workout routine and stick to a very healthy lifestyle. Last year I was diagnosed with a depression and put on antidepressants. It really slowed me down. My depression got under control but I started gaining weight. The belly fat became an issue! That‚Äôs why I decided to try CoolSculpting.

Here are my answers to all the questions you asked me: ‚úÖ How much is it?¬†This really depends on how many areas you treat and how many times you decide to treat the area. @SkinSpirit offers my followers $100 off when you mention @anyasfashionhobby ‚úÖ Does it hurt?¬†I was a little worried thinking that my first treatment was going to be uncomfortable because I had no idea how my body would react. I have a pretty high pain tolerance and overall I didn‚Äôt think it was bad at all. Madison @mind.body.madison made me feel very comfortable ‚úÖ What does it feel like? It literally feels like you‚Äôre sitting outside in the middle of winter and someone took a vacuum hose and stuck it on your stomach. It is called Cool Sculpting so most people get cold! The suction squeezing is what feels uncomfortable more than the cold. Once that area goes numb¬†you don‚Äôt feel much at all ‚úÖ How long does the procedure take?¬†The procedure is only about 35 minutes per area ‚úÖ How long does it take to see results?¬†This is the perfect time to start CoolSculpting. After each area is treated it takes about 90 days to see the full results. After about 45 days you can decide if you want to treat the area again .

caption:
One of my favorite parts of this whole process is combining things that at commercial and reproducible with elements that have a handmade feel. One of the questions I get most often when I tell people what I do is ‚ÄúDo you write every invitation by hand?!‚Äù The answer is a HARD no {although if your budget is in the five figures, feel free to hit me up üòÇ}. If you‚Äôre still wanting to learn about digitizing or vectorizing your calligraphy or other artwork, check out the in-depth tutorial on our YouTube channel via the link in our stories or Doorbell highlights!!!! And let me know what else you‚Äôd like to learn too - I talked about prepping files for foil or letterpress printing in stories today, and those will be available in the Printing highlight for as long as you need them!.

It‚Äôs right before bedtime so you know what that means - another Insta post for the day! Our ‚Äú25 Ways to Grow Your IG Following‚Äù video is live on @youtube (see it in stories or linked in profile), and there‚Äôs one tip that rises above all the other ones: BE CONSISTENT. There is no one thing to do that will definitely work, there is no way to buy yourself legit, authentic followers who will turn into clients. There is no overnight fix for growing a real base on any platform, and anyone who tells you there is is lying. But the one thing that will pay off is consistency, mixed with a little evaluation and common sense. Do what works, pay attention, and then do it again and again as you continue to grow and you will see results - I‚Äôve had to enact this same strategy in so many other areas of my life, and consistent hard work SUCKS sometimes but it‚Äôs the best strategy in almost any arena (work, relationships, skin care, fitness), and Insta is no exception! Check out the video and let us know what you think üëåüèΩ.
.
.

caption:
Looking back on 2018 (is it already time for that?) and releasing this Paper Crane Wax Seal with @waxseals and @artisaire is a huge highlight of the year for DbyL! This design is so close to our heart - did you know that people make origami Cranes as a symbol of hope, new beginnings, and prosperity? If you‚Äôve ever walked by the site of a recent tragedy, chances are you‚Äôve seen ropes of them, and people often bring them as wedding gifts as well. If you make 1,000 of them, you get to make a wish! This was the first thing I thought of when considering what someone would want on the outside of their incoming mail - wedding invites, get well soon cards, baby announcements - hope, prosperity, new beginnings, indeed. This baby is linked in my stories or Profile and you can find it at @waxseals or @minted evenüëåüèΩ It‚Äôs also part of their styling kit that has over 20 wax seals in the most popular colors for amazing styling!
.

caption:
Happy New Year! Our annual Goals blog will be up soon but for now, here‚Äôs a recap of the Awesomeness that was 2018! -Hit 10k the week of my Birthday! And we‚Äôre thiiis close to 18k meaning we pretty much doubled this year!!! HI all of you and THANK YOU and WHY are you here?! Tell us, we are so flabbergasted and humbled and grateful!
-Gave away free wedding invites (should we do this again?! What would you want?)
-Launched The Collections - the wrong way! This was a huge learning experience for us but so worth it, and allowed us to re-launch in November in a MUCH better way!
-Created #nomoreboringenvelopes ! What a fun exercise/challenge! Check out the hashtag if you have no idea what I‚Äôm talking about...and send NOT boring snail mail if ya can!
-Got political!
-Learned to laser cut
-Brought on @madalynyatesphoto !!! The best decision of the year, by far.
-Created 18,000 pieces for 62+ events ! Wow!!! To answer my most frequently asked question - HELL NO I do not write them all by hand!
-Gave back more than ever as a business.
-Made Custom @vans with our art printed on them (how freaking cool?!)
-Collab‚Äôd with awesome boss ladies like @jennythenutritionist and @suiteonestudio to name VERY few
-Worked with some of the best planners (no offense but too many to name!!!)
-Further developed my style and ideal client profile. Became more comfortable with watercolors, pricing, and who I am as an artist. Started teaching mini-moments via Instagram and YouTube !
-Released our Paper Crane wax seal with @artisaire ‚Äòs Creative Community, which got picked up by @Minted for their collection!
-Traveled to LA, Italy, Czech Republic, Poland, Utah, Wyoming, Montana, Savannah, San Diego, New York, and I‚Äôm sure I‚Äôm forgetting several places...
-Worked out 200 times!
...and most importantly, maintained a much better relationship with my work and mental health overall!
.
.
.

Bio: Founder of @fashionablefit_training || Creative director #fashionablefitcollection @nellycom || My Zalando Sportsdrobe
caption:
My workout routine? Some of you often ask how my running/weight split looks like in a week. This really depends on my focus and or what my body feels like doing. Usually I will do 3-4 weight workouts per week (mostly high rep circuit style training). I‚Äôve always loved high intensity workouts that will have me sweating üí™üèºüí¶üí¶ I run about 2-3 times per week. Usually one long distance run (anything between 8km - 20km depending on if I‚Äôm on a marathon program or not). I love intervals/ sprints so I will do this probably twice a week. Sometimes it‚Äôs just finishing off a weight workout with 10 x 30:30 sprints on the treadmill. And sometimes it‚Äôs a proper interval session for 40-60 min and then that‚Äôs my workout. 
I would say I generally train 45-60 min 4-5 times per week. It really depends on the week. This past Sunday I ran 17km and I haven‚Äôt felt like training since... So some weeks I‚Äôll have a rest week and some weeks I‚Äôm very active. For me it‚Äôs all about having a holistic approach to a healthy lifestyle. I have my rituals and my regime that forms a foundation for most weeks. And investing my time in maintaining that is something I prioritize as it adds so much positivity to my overall well-being. Having that said listening to my body and being flexible has been key in finding a sustainable/balanced lifestyle that is just naturally maintainable all year round. Hope this helps! üñ§üí™üèºüí¶ || Get my outfit in my @zalando shop (link in bio)

Bio: Founder of @fashionablefit_training || Creative director #fashionablefitcollection @nellycom || My Zalando Sportsdrobe
caption:
My motivation to exercise is fueled by something bigger than performance and superficial goals. I would say a healthy and happy life is my motivation - still, it‚Äôs okay to want to be strong, to run fast or to have abs and I have those goals too! But in my experience, it‚Äôs difficult to stay motivated when these are the only reasons to work out. 
Some days are going to be tough and you won‚Äôt feel like you have the motivation to exercise. However, these might be the days you need it the most for your psychological wellbeing. It‚Äôs amazing what training does to our body and brain and how by only moving your body for 30 minutes can shift your mindset and make you feel good. I have designed three workouts that can be your go-to when you don‚Äôt feel like you have the motivation, or simply, when you‚Äôre in need of a getaway to mental bliss. Basically, these workouts can be your happy pill and a rush of positive emotions. You just follow the workout and I promise that you will feel that your mindset shifts and how it positively affects your mental wellness. I‚Äôm pretty sure you will get addicted to these feel-good hormones just like me! caption:

üìç@vaquerodining
üî™ Chef @damon_porter & @chef_maryann

Oh where to begin... First off, please bookmark this in @eatclubapp I did and  scored the 50% offer, yes this app has changed me.
.
We began our date night over a beautifully plated dish of quail testicals on a fresh langos. Ok, first question no doubt is "what is it like". Simply put it's like an egg yolk, yes it pops üòÇ. Rubbery, and very egg white like in taste... Any way, it was delicious with the yogurt üòÇ.
.
Back on track, we properly started with Mary Anns freshly baked sourdough bread and butter ‚ù§Ô∏è. The best way to start a meal üçû.
.
For mains we had the Roasted Figs & Blue Cheese Tortillini, balanced with currants, pinenuts, and vincotto. It's not overpowering with that blue cheese punch, but the main reason I got this is because they do not do many pastas here... But when they do üëå.
.
The other main was the dry aged steak (of course, @espresso_and_matcha goto üòÇ). I was tossing up which photo to use, but I really loved the slicing of one of the tender meat slabs ü§§ (also Instagram limit of 10 images lol). Also not shown, the black garlic parfait, oh my... That should be a side on its own... it's a dream, and I could eat it daily ‚ù§Ô∏è.
.
Desserts, I saw "Blueberries" and "chocolatey goodness" so I had to have it, I mean it sounds like I wrote it üòÇ. Even pulled out my phone to illuminate this beautiful dish. So much to love with the luscious chocolatey goodness, poached pears, coffee and fresh blueberries. And Espresso had her signature Espresso Martini üòÇüëå.
.
I'm glad I live so close, would definitely continue coming back üòä.
.

Name: feedmedearly
Bio: NYC-based // Food + Travel + Wellness // Personal @xo.love.jess
caption:
Feeling profoundly grateful for so many things. I posted yesterday about my friend who passed away from cancer this week, thank you so much for your sweet comments; I‚Äôm so lucky to have had her in my life. I‚Äôm grateful in hindsight that my own cancer experience taught me to live so fully, and to be so vulnerable. I firmly believe that vulnerability paves the way for great life experiences. True friendships aren‚Äôt made on the sidelines, they‚Äôre made when you get to the core of another human being and you share things ‚Äì the dreams and the disappointments ‚Äì that aren‚Äôt so often shared. Coming out of this 10-day visit to Portland, I'm grateful for a new set of friendships that I know will stand the test of time. Zeph the butcher @proletariatmeat who dropped everything to help us cook and set up for our Secret Supper dinner. Max @rootsandcrownspdx who was the most interesting drinking buddy I could have asked for‚Ä¶.+ countless others who shared their time and their stories with me.
_______
Including this guy...chef Troy MacLarty from @bollywoodtheaterpdx who joined us on our media trip with @traveloregon down to the central coast. Over the course of 3 days, we drove, we ate, we drank, we saw whales, and we staked out a pretty amazing friendship along the way. There were no walls, no fronts, just really great conversations about the stuff in life that matters. And then he fed me all the Bollywood snacksüí™üèª. If you‚Äôre in town, make this place your first stop, it‚Äôs the best food I ate all week, no BS. Although I may be a little bit biased at this point ;) Peace out Oregon, #alwaysand4ever

caption: TERRARIUM || a terrarium is a miniature garden created in an artificial environment. We made this beautiful terrarium in a plastic mason-style jar. It's complete with real plants, stickers, tiny figures and REAL plants that you grow from seeds. It has been so fun watching this grow over the past couple of days. You can see the roots growing down through the soil, sand and rocks, and we have watched the seeds sprout and grow towards the sun. This is a fabulous product that we highly recommend. It's from @bigwaustralia  @shamrockaustralia and @creativityforkidsaustralia

caption: ELMER'S OOEY GOOEY SLIME || one of the most common question I get asked by family, friends and followers is "Jacinta, do you have a good slime recipe?" I tried making this glittery pink slime today (while the kids were at school to avoid disappointing them - again!) and it worked perfectly. The process was mess free and the products are non-toxic. Slime making will be the perfect boredom busting activity for the upcoming school holidays! And, did you know that Elmer's is running Australia's first Ooey Gluey Slimes Games with lots of prizes to be won. Head to http://www.elmersslimegames.com.au or tap the link in my profile for more information. #OGSlimeGames #ElmersAU

caption: Honestly: I‚Äôd been dreading this afternoon. I‚Äôve had my hands totally full with the girls and work deadlines and trying to get our house ready to put on the market (üôÄ), and then last night, I realized I had scheduled Scarlett‚Äôs dentist appointment for this afternoon. Her last few visits were less than fun, since one of them was an emergency visit followed by several follow-up visits and x-rays after she took a face dive into a wood table a couple of months back. Thankfully, she healed amazingly well, but the dentist has not been her favorite place since. ü¶∑ Needless to say, I assumed today would be no different. I thought about cancelling the appointment. I nearly turned the car around in frustration on the way there as Scarlett started to panic and insisted she didn‚Äôt need an X-ray. I forgot the stroller to have a place for Emme during the appointment, or rather, there was no room in our car for the stroller since the entire trunk is lined with bags, ready for donation after the multi-room purge we did on Monday and Tuesday. The thought of attempting to handle a crying 4 year old, unwilling to sit for an x-ray, coupled with a 17-month old, unwilling to sit period, had me wondering why the heck I had thought this was a good idea. üò≠ And you know what? They were great. Like, really, really great. üëåüèª And of course, that won‚Äôt always be the case; but today was a victory, and my oldest baby was so brave, so we went to @wholefoods, picked up dinner and celebratory vegan cupcakes and Scarlett sang all the way through our shop. You can catch part of her performance in tonight‚Äôs #instastory. The point is, sometimes I don‚Äôt give them enough credit. Sometimes they‚Äôre just kids, and days are hard. But man, I love them ALL OF THE DANG TIME. üëßüèªüë∂üèªüéÄüòç‚ù§Ô∏è

caption:
I'm now on a diet. I'm not a diet person, but this is hopefully for the good of bub and his eczema. Cutting out his allergies from my diet as he's still breastfed and hoping for some radically good changes to his behaviour, sleep and skin. The immunologist told me to do the creams and see how he goes and there was just no improvement. In fact, he was getting worse, then better, then worse. I needed to do something.
It's only been about a week, but it's so hard!
I'm so used to eating so many things with milk in them! 
Did you know pesto has milk (and one had cashews)?! Honestly, I was nearly in tears at the grocery store yesterday just trying to find something that I would like.
Here's to hope for better things (and a happier, less itchy baby) really soon!
.
.
.

caption:
Lesson 4 of 2018. 
There‚Äôs never a right way to do the wrong thing. 
Many of you know our commitment to animal rescue. Many of you know we‚Äôve traveled the entire country to thank the people doing the hard work. So when we hear from people that disagree with our slogan to ‚ÄúMake Rescues The Breed Of Choice‚Äù, it hurts. But we also realize that breeders and the public have a right to their opinion. Our opinion however is that there is never a right way to do the wrong thing. That‚Äôs what we stand for. That‚Äôs what we are made of. And we will continue to promote animal rescue in a fun way by simply showing rescued pets aren‚Äôt damaged. We will promote animal rescue by showing how one...or two animals can change your life. And so the lesson is don‚Äôt veer from your principles to appeal to the masses. Change the world by being different. #2019goals #2travelingdogs #adoptdontshop #rv #rvwithdogs @theellenshow @animalplanet

caption: This morning, I woke up and broke a wine glass I had mistakenly left too close to the edge of the RV counter. I left it too close to the edge because I had no room in the sink because I was too lazy to do dishes. I was too lazy to do dishes because I spent hours making a vegan dinner of jackfruit bbq, vegan macaroni and cheese and collard greens. Because you know. I was hungry from working all day, sitting out in the cold working by a campfire because Brickle likes to be outside the RV. All. The. Time. Yet, he can‚Äôt be trusted alone not to scare children and campground visitors with his protective barking. So yeah. I didn‚Äôt do the dishes last night because I was too tired and didn‚Äôt want to wash them outside in 30 degrees because we have no sewer hookup here and are parked in this spot for 3 weeks. On a hill. And we don‚Äôt want to move this thing to go to a dump station. But after all that, I get to wake up to these two. I get to hike with them. Write a blog for them. And try to save some lives today. But it‚Äôs gonna be difficult because my only laptop computer decided to break yesterday too. So yeah. Good morning, y‚Äôall! Did you do the dishes last night?! #2travelingdogs #rvlife #camping #wednesdaywisdom #dogsofinstagram #rv @apple
